---  
description: Use when creating, validating, or debugging a Component GraphQL Query for Sitecore list components and parent-child datasource structures.  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
Use `ComponentQuery` only for list / parent-child datasource components.  
  
Do NOT use `ComponentQuery` for:  
- simple single-datasource components  
- context-only components  
  
Expected query shape:  
- Query name matches parent template name  
- Variables: `$datasource: String!`, `$language: String!`  
- Root alias: `datasource: item(path: $datasource, language: $language)`  
- Parent fragment: `... on <ParentTemplateName>`  
- Child items under:  
  `children { results { ... on <ChildTemplateName> { ... } } }`  
  
Rules:  
- Use PascalCase for template names in fragments  
- Use camelCase for field names in the GraphQL query  
- Wrap editable fields in `{ jsonValue }`  
- Include `id` in child results  
- Children live at `fields.data.datasource.children.results`  
  
Checklist before saving:  
- Query syntax is valid  
- Braces and parentheses match  
- No trailing commas  
- Parent template fragment matches Sitecore template name  
- Child template fragment matches Sitecore template name  
- No collision-prone field names like `icon` or `name`  
- Every needed field is explicitly queried  
  
Failure symptoms:  
- If children are missing, the query is empty or incomplete.  
- If `page.layout.sitecore.route` becomes undefined, suspect malformed `ComponentQuery`.  